Hobie Beach in Port Elizabeth following a drowning this evening Picture: Supplied The search for the body of a 22-year-old man, who went missing and is presumed to have drowned at Hobie beach earlier this evening, will continue tomorrow. According to a NMB Water Emergency Rescue Committee report, three men went to the beach, with two of them entering the water close to Shark Rock Pier. The report said one of the men was swept towards the concrete pillars while the other disappeared between the waves and never re-surfaced. Police spokesperson Colonel Priscilla Naidu said police divers had been called to the beach after receiving a report that someone had gone into the sea and had not returned. She said the search would continue on Thursday. Related